<br>
They left out things that I would like to have seen (Barrow wights, Bombadil, the real development of the relationship between Gimli and Legolas), but in the end it didnt detract fromthe movie.  It was no Tolkien &quot;by the letter&quot;, but it was Tolkien &quot;by the spirit&quot;.  <br>
<br>
The only drawback was all the idiot parents that brought their 6-10 year olds to the matinee showing to see &quot;elves and cute hobbits&quot;, and got the bejeebers scared out of them by the brutal combat and bloodletting, and the deaths.  When Bilbo &quot;changes&quot; for that brief moment, one of the ones behind me screamed, and her mother had to take her (probably 7 years old) and her toddler sister out of the theater, gibbering in fright<br>
<br>
For God's sake, the movie is PG-13 for a reason.  <br>
<br>
Luckily the second showing had few of the stupid parents there, and none sitting near me.<br>
