<br>
SHAME on all you folk who saw the movie before reading the books! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   The movie was really great, no doubt of that, but the books are still better.  The books are just a little more in-depth than the movie.  And the movie makes a lot more sense if you see it with knowledge from the books.<br>
<br>
Legolas was one of, if not the coolest guy in the movie.  My favorite part was when he took an arrow from the quiver, thrust it into the orce eye, pulled it out again, and then shot it at another orc!  OH MAN!  what a total badass!  Beregond was played really well too, he had some really neat scenes as well.  Aragorn was everything I expected him to be.  The scene at the inn when he is smoking, and his face lights up was absolutely perfect!  I didn't like the role Gimli had in the movie, he seemed almost like a dead weight, but he did have some of the best lines in the whole movie.  &quot;No one throws the dwarf!&quot;  Followed immediately after by, &quot;NOT THE BEARD!&quot;  In the next few movies, he is gonna be really cool.<br>
<br>
That agent smith guy was also the main character in Priscilla: Queen of the Desert.  he played a drag queen looking for a venue.  Try seeing him play that role, then watch the matrix, and you realize what an amazing actor he is <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
